('AN0000976', 'WC0000976', 'ADV0026', '2025-12-11 19:52:01.097', 'IN_PERSON', '22', 'Client, Advisor', 'Annual tax planning session with client and their CPA. Reviewed YTD realized gains and losses. Identified opportunities for tax-loss harvesting totaling approximately $5976. Discussed Roth conversion strategy given clients lower income this year. Agreed to convert $50,000 from Traditional IRA to Roth before year end.', 'Tax planning session; TLH opportunities identified; Roth conversion planned', '1) Execute tax-loss harvesting trades. 2) Process Roth conversion. 3) Coordinate with CPA on documentation.', '2026-04-12', 'Portfolio Review, Asset Allocation, Estate Planning', 'POSITIVE', '2026-02-17 14:32:01.097'),
('AN0000977', 'WC0000977', 'ADV0027', '2025-12-11 18:12:01.097', 'EMAIL_FOLLOW_UP', '29', 'Client, Spouse, Advisor', 'Proactive outreach following Fed interest rate announcement. Explained potential impact on bond portfolio and overall allocation. Client appreciated the communication. Reviewed current fixed income holdings - duration is appropriate given outlook. No immediate changes needed but will continue monitoring.', 'Rate decision follow-up; no changes needed to fixed income', '1) Continue monitoring rates. 2) Send monthly fixed income update. 3) Review duration in 60 days.', '2026-04-15', 'Goal Progress, Cash Flow, Market Update', 'NEUTRAL', '2026-02-17 14:32:01.097'),
('AN0000978', 'WC0000978', 'ADV0028', '2025-12-11 16:32:01.097', 'ANNUAL_REVIEW', '36', 'Client, Advisor, Portfolio Manager', 'Client approaching retirement in 18 months. Detailed discussion of income strategy and Social Security timing. Ran multiple scenarios showing impact of claiming at 62 vs 67 vs 70. Recommended delaying to age 67 given health history and portfolio size. Began transitioning portfolio toward more income-generating positions.', 'Pre-retirement planning; Social Security timing analyzed; income strategy begun', '1) Begin portfolio transition to income focus. 2) Finalize Social Security filing date. 3) Create retirement income projection.', '2026-04-18', 'Market Volatility, Risk Tolerance, Long-term Strategy', 'CONCERNED', '2026-02-17 14:32:01.097'),
('AN0000979', 'WC0000979', 'ADV0029', '2025-12-11 14:52:01.097', 'QUARTERLY_CHECK_IN', '43', 'Client, Advisor, Tax Specialist', 'Follow-up on previous discussion about charitable giving strategy. Client wishes to donate $10979 to alma mater. Reviewed options including direct gift, donor-advised fund, and qualified charitable distribution from IRA. Recommended QCD given clients age (72) and RMD requirements. Will coordinate with charity for proper documentation.', 'Charitable giving strategy; recommending QCD for $10979 donation', '1) Coordinate QCD with charity. 2) Obtain tax documentation. 3) Confirm receipt of funds.', '2026-04-21', 'Liquidity Needs, Tax Planning, Withdrawal Strategy', 'POSITIVE', '2026-02-17 14:32:01.097'),
('AN0000980', 'WC0000980', 'ADV0030', '2025-12-11 13:12:01.097', 'PHONE_CALL', '50', 'Client, Advisor', 'Conducted comprehensive annual portfolio review with client. Reviewed performance versus benchmarks - portfolio outperformed by 1.2% YTD. Discussed asset allocation and confirmed it remains aligned with stated risk tolerance. Client expressed satisfaction with current strategy but inquired about increasing international exposure. Recommended gradual shift of 5% from domestic to international equities over next quarter. Also discussed estate planning updates needed following birth of grandchild.', 'Annual review complete; increasing intl exposure 5%; estate planning update needed', '1) Implement 5% shift to international. 2) Contact estate attorney for document updates. 3) Schedule follow-up in 90 days.', '2026-04-24', 'Estate Planning, Beneficiaries, Education Funding', 'VERY_POSITIVE', '2026-02-17 14:32:01.097'),
('AN0000981', 'WC0000981', 'ADV0031', '2025-12-11 11:32:01.097', 'VIDEO_CONFERENCE', '57', 'Client, Spouse, Advisor', 'Quarterly check-in call. Markets have been volatile but client portfolio has held up well due to diversification. Client mentioned potential job change that could impact cash flow needs. Discussed contingency plans including reducing contributions temporarily if needed. Reviewed progress on retirement goal - currently at 72% of target with 8 years to go. On track assuming 7% average returns.', 'Quarterly check-in; potential job change discussed; retirement goal on track at 72%', '1) Monitor employment situation. 2) Prepare contingency cash flow scenarios. 3) Next quarterly call in October.', '2026-04-27', 'ESG Investing, Values Alignment, Portfolio Transition', 'POSITIVE', '2026-02-17 14:32:01.097'),
('AN0000982', 'WC0000982', 'ADV0032', '2025-12-11 09:52:01.097', 'IN_PERSON', '64', 'Client, Advisor, Portfolio Manager', 'Client called with concerns about recent market downturn. Took time to review historical market corrections and long-term performance data. Emphasized importance of staying invested and avoiding emotional decisions. Client seemed reassured after discussion. Reminded them of their 15+ year time horizon and conservative allocation already in place. No changes to portfolio recommended at this time.', 'Client concerns addressed re: market volatility; no portfolio changes', '1) Send market perspective article. 2) Check in again in 2 weeks. 3) No portfolio changes.', '2026-04-30', 'Tax Optimization, Roth Conversion, Loss Harvesting', 'NEUTRAL', '2026-02-17 14:32:01.097'),
