('AN0002961', 'WC0000961', 'ADV0011', '2025-07-27 00:32:01.097', 'VIDEO_CONFERENCE', '42', 'Client, Spouse, Advisor', 'Quarterly check-in call. Markets have been volatile but client portfolio has held up well due to diversification. Client mentioned potential job change that could impact cash flow needs. Discussed contingency plans including reducing contributions temporarily if needed. Reviewed progress on retirement goal - currently at 72% of target with 8 years to go. On track assuming 7% average returns.', 'Quarterly check-in; potential job change discussed; retirement goal on track at 72%', '1) Monitor employment situation. 2) Prepare contingency cash flow scenarios. 3) Next quarterly call in October.', '2026-05-09', 'Goal Progress, Cash Flow, Market Update', 'POSITIVE', '2026-02-17 14:32:01.097'),
('AN0002962', 'WC0000962', 'ADV0012', '2025-07-26 22:52:01.097', 'IN_PERSON', '49', 'Client, Advisor, Portfolio Manager', 'Client called with concerns about recent market downturn. Took time to review historical market corrections and long-term performance data. Emphasized importance of staying invested and avoiding emotional decisions. Client seemed reassured after discussion. Reminded them of their 15+ year time horizon and conservative allocation already in place. No changes to portfolio recommended at this time.', 'Client concerns addressed re: market volatility; no portfolio changes', '1) Send market perspective article. 2) Check in again in 2 weeks. 3) No portfolio changes.', '2026-05-12', 'Market Volatility, Risk Tolerance, Long-term Strategy', 'NEUTRAL', '2026-02-17 14:32:01.097'),
('AN0002963', 'WC0000963', 'ADV0013', '2025-07-26 21:12:01.097', 'EMAIL_FOLLOW_UP', '56', 'Client, Advisor, Tax Specialist', 'Video call to discuss upcoming liquidity needs. Client planning major home renovation estimated at $52963. Reviewed options including portfolio withdrawal vs. home equity line. Recommended combination approach to minimize tax impact. Will prepare detailed cash flow analysis showing optimal withdrawal strategy across accounts.', 'Home renovation funding strategy discussed; preparing cash flow analysis', '1) Prepare detailed withdrawal strategy analysis. 2) Model tax implications. 3) Meet again in 2 weeks with recommendations.', '2026-05-15', 'Liquidity Needs, Tax Planning, Withdrawal Strategy', 'CONCERNED', '2026-02-17 14:32:01.097'),
